In [364]:
Age_bins = pd.cut(df.Age[df.Age.notnull()], range(-1,100), labels=range(0,100))
df_Age = pd.concat([Age_bins, df.Survived[df.Age.notnull()]], axis = 1)
df_Age['Survival_Rate'] = df_Age.apply(lambda x: df_Age.Survived[(df_Age.Age == x.Age)].mean(), axis = 1)

data = df_Age[['Age','Survival_Rate']][df_Age.Survived.notnull()]
plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))

plt.scatter(df_Age.Age[(df_Age.Age <= 17)], df_Age.Survival_Rate[(df_Age.Age <= 17)])
plt.scatter(df_Age.Age[(df_Age.Age > 17) & (df_Age.Age <= 45)], 
            df_Age.Survival_Rate[(df_Age.Age > 17) & (df_Age.Age <= 45)])
plt.scatter(df_Age.Age[(df_Age.Age > 45)], df_Age.Survival_Rate[(df_Age.Age > 45)]);

map_title = {'Mr.':'Mr',
             'Miss.': "Miss",
             'Mrs.': "Mrs",
             'Dona.': "Mrs",
             'Master.': 'Master',

             'the Countess.': "Other1",
             'Mlle.': "Other1",
             'Ms.': "Other1",
             'Mme.': "Other1",
             'Lady.': "Other1",
             'Sir.': "Other1",

             'Dr.': "Other2",
             'Col.': 'Other2',
             'Major.': 'Other2',

             'Don.': "Other3",
             'Capt.': 'Other3',
             'Jonkheer.': "Other3",
             'Rev.': "Other3"}

df_prepped['title'] = title = df["Name"].apply(lambda x: x.split(", ")[1].split(". ")[0]+'.')
df_prepped.title = df_prepped.title.map(map_title)
df_prepped.title = df_prepped.title.astype('category')

2. Modeling¶

In [405]:
x = df_train_prepped.drop('Survived', axis=1)
y = df_train_prepped['Survived']

Accuracy = {}

Naive Bayes¶

In [406]:
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB, MultinomialNB, BernoulliNB
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score

#Gaussian
GNB = GaussianNB()
scores = cross_val_score(GNB, x, y, cv=5)
accuracyGNB = scores.mean()
print("Gaussian Naive Bayes Accuracy :", accuracyGNB)

#Multinomial
MNB = MultinomialNB()
scores = cross_val_score(MNB, x, y, cv=5)
accuracyMNB = scores.mean()
print("Multinomial Naive Bayes Accuracy :", accuracyMNB)

#Bernoulli
BNB = BernoulliNB()
scores = cross_val_score(BNB, x, y, cv=5)
accuracyBNB = scores.mean()
print("Bernoulli Naive Bayes Accuracy :", accuracyBNB)

#Plot accuracies corresponding to various naive bayes methods
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(8,5))
fig = sns.barplot(y=[accuracyGNB, accuracyMNB, accuracyBNB], x=["GaussianNB", "MultinomialNB", "BernoulliNB"], ax=ax1)
fig.set(xlabel="Naive Bayes Methods", ylabel="Accuracy")

# #Finally we decide to use Bernoulli Naive Bayes

KNN¶

In [407]:
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score

accuracy = []
k_value = []

for k in range(3, int(np.sqrt(len(x)+1))):
    kNN = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k)
    scores = cross_val_score(kNN, x, y, cv=10)
    accuracy.append(scores.mean())
    k_value.append(k)

#Plot accuracies corresponding to value of K
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15,5))
fig = sns.pointplot(y=accuracy, x=k_value, ax=ax1)
fig.set(xlabel="K Value", ylabel="Accuracy")

print("Maximum Accuracy :", max(accuracy))
print("Value of K corresponding to maximum accuracy :", k_value[accuracy.index(max(accuracy))])

#Final value of K must correspond to maximum accuracy.
kNN = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k_value[accuracy.index(max(accuracy))])
scores = cross_val_score(kNN, x, y, cv=5)
accuracy = scores.mean()
print("K Nearest Neighbor Accuracy :", accuracy)

# Recored {"kNN":accuracy}
Accuracy["kNN"] = accuracy

Maximum Accuracy : 0.801430030644
Value of K corresponding to maximum accuracy : 9
K Nearest Neighbor Accuracy : 0.785704487608

from sklearn import svm
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score

x = df_train_prepped.drop('Survived', axis=1)
y = df_train_prepped['Survived']

#Linear Kernel
SVML = svm.SVC(kernel="linear")
scores = cross_val_score(SVML, x, y, cv=5)
accuracySVML = scores.mean()
print("Support Vector Machine Accuracy (Linear Kernel) :", accuracySVML)

#RBF Kernel
SVMR = svm.SVC(kernel="rbf")
scores = cross_val_score(SVMR, x, y, cv=5)
accuracySVMR = scores.mean()
print("Support Vector Machine Accuracy (RBF Kernel) :", accuracySVMR)

#Polynomial Kernel
SVMP = svm.SVC(kernel="poly")
scores = cross_val_score(SVMP, x, y, cv=5)
accuracySVMP = scores.mean()
print("Support Vector Machine Accuracy (Poly Kernel) :", accuracySVMP)

#Plot accuracies corresponding to various naive bayes methods
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(8,5))
fig = sns.barplot(y=[accuracySVML, accuracySVMR, accuracySVMP], x=["Linear", "RBF", "Polynomial"], ax=ax1)
fig.set(xlabel="Kernels", ylabel="Accuracy")

#Finally we decide to use Polynomial Kernel
Accuracy["supportVectorMachine"] = accuracySVMP
